{"readme":"<h1 class=\"title\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://github.com/mattdesl/glsl-earth\">glsl-earth</a><div class=\"contrib\"></div></h1>\n<p><a href=\"http://github.com/badges/stability-badges\"></a></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://i.imgur.com/uz2WYlL.png\" alt=\"earth\"></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://glslb.in/s/a92ee62b\">(glslbin demo)</a></p>\n<p>Quickly get a spinning Earth-like planet on a black background in GLSL. This is not distance field rendering, just a 2D effect.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-glsl\"><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span>precision&#xA0;mediump&#xA0;</span><span class=\"storage type glsl\"><span>float</span></span><span>;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"storage modifier glsl\"><span>uniform</span></span><span>&#xA0;</span><span class=\"storage type glsl\"><span>float</span></span><span>&#xA0;iGlobalTime;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"storage modifier glsl\"><span>uniform</span></span><span>&#xA0;</span><span class=\"storage type glsl\"><span>vec3</span></span><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;iResolution;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span>#</span><span class=\"meta preprocessor keyword import define glsl\"><span>pragma&#xA0;glslify:</span></span><span class=\"entity name function glsl\"><span>&#xA0;planet&#xA0;</span></span><span class=\"operator glsl\"><span>=&#xA0;</span></span><span class=\"keyword operator glsl\"><span>require</span></span><span>(</span><span class=\"string quoted double\"><span>&apos;glsl-earth&apos;</span></span><span>)</span><span>&#xA0;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"storage type glsl\"><span>void</span></span><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"punctuation whitespace function leading c\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span><span class=\"entity name function c\"><span>main</span></span><span class=\"meta parens c\"><span class=\"punctuation section parens begin c\"><span>(</span></span><span class=\"punctuation section parens end c\"><span>)</span></span></span><span>&#xA0;</span><span class=\"meta block c\"><span class=\"punctuation section block begin c\"><span>{</span></span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;</span><span class=\"storage type glsl\"><span>vec2</span></span><span>&#xA0;uv&#xA0;=&#xA0;</span><span class=\"support variable glsl\"><span>gl_FragCoord</span></span><span class=\"punctuation separator variable-access c\"><span>.</span></span><span class=\"variable other dot-access c\"><span>xy</span></span><span>&#xA0;/&#xA0;iResolution</span><span class=\"punctuation separator variable-access c\"><span>.</span></span><span class=\"variable other dot-access c\"><span>xy</span></span><span>;</span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span class=\"punctuation whitespace comment leading c++\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;</span></span><span class=\"comment line double-slash c++\"><span class=\"punctuation definition comment c++\"><span>//</span></span><span>the&#xA0;rotation</span><span>&#xA0;</span></span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;</span><span class=\"storage type glsl\"><span>vec2</span></span><span>&#xA0;rot&#xA0;=</span><span class=\"meta function-call c\"><span class=\"punctuation whitespace function-call leading c\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span><span class=\"support function any-method c\"><span>vec2</span></span><span>(</span></span><span>iGlobalTime*</span><span class=\"constant numeric c\"><span>0.03</span></span><span>,&#xA0;iGlobalTime*</span><span class=\"constant numeric c\"><span>0.01</span></span><span>);</span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span class=\"punctuation whitespace comment leading c++\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;</span></span><span class=\"comment line double-slash c++\"><span class=\"punctuation definition comment c++\"><span>//</span></span><span>%&#xA0;of&#xA0;screen</span><span>&#xA0;</span></span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;</span><span class=\"storage type glsl\"><span>float</span></span><span>&#xA0;size&#xA0;=&#xA0;</span><span class=\"constant numeric c\"><span>0.75</span></span><span>;</span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span class=\"punctuation whitespace comment leading c++\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;</span></span><span class=\"comment line double-slash c++\"><span class=\"punctuation definition comment c++\"><span>//</span></span><span>create&#xA0;our&#xA0;planet</span><span>&#xA0;</span></span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;</span><span class=\"storage type glsl\"><span>vec3</span></span><span>&#xA0;color&#xA0;=</span><span class=\"meta function-call c\"><span class=\"punctuation whitespace function-call leading c\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span><span class=\"support function any-method c\"><span>planet</span></span><span>(</span></span><span>uv,&#xA0;iResolution</span><span class=\"punctuation separator variable-access c\"><span>.</span></span><span class=\"variable other dot-access c\"><span>xy</span></span><span>,&#xA0;size,&#xA0;rot);</span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;</span><span class=\"support variable glsl\"><span>gl_FragColor</span></span><span class=\"punctuation separator variable-access c\"><span>.</span></span><span class=\"variable other dot-access c\"><span>rgb</span></span><span>&#xA0;=&#xA0;color;</span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;</span><span class=\"support variable glsl\"><span>gl_FragColor</span></span><span class=\"punctuation separator variable-access c\"><span>.</span></span><span class=\"variable other dot-access c\"><span>a</span></span><span>&#xA0;=&#xA0;</span><span class=\"constant numeric c\"><span>1.0</span></span><span>;</span></span></span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"meta block c\"><span class=\"punctuation section block end c\"><span>}</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n</code></pre>\n<p>PRs welcome for improvements/optimizations.</p>\n<h2 id=\"usage\">Usage</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/glsl-earth\"></a></p>\n<h4 id=\"-vec3-color-planet-vec2-uv-vec2-resolution-float-size-vec2-rotation-\"><code>vec3 color = planet(vec2 uv, vec2 resolution, float size, vec2 rotation)</code></h4>\n<p>Gets a planet based on the screen <code>uv</code> and <code>resolution</code>. The <code>size</code> is how big the planet shoul be, where 1.0 fits the screen. <code>rotation</code> is how much to rotate the planet.</p>\n<h4 id=\"-vec3-color-planet-vec2-uv-vec2-resolution-float-size-\"><code>vec3 color = planet(vec2 uv, vec2 resolution, float size)</code></h4>\n<p>The same as above but with no rotation.</p>\n<h4 id=\"-vec3-color-planet-vec2-uv-vec2-resolution-\"><code>vec3 color = planet(vec2 uv, vec2 resolution)</code></h4>\n<p>The same as above but with no rotation and a default size of 1.0</p>\n<h2 id=\"license\">License</h2>\n<p>MIT, see <a href=\"http://github.com/mattdesl/glsl-earth/blob/master/LICENSE.md\">LICENSE.md</a> for details.</p>\n"}